    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe builtin treesitter support doesn't currently have any functionality for indentation. \n\nThe treesitter tree can provide information that is useful for determining the correct indentation, so it seems like a logical feature to have.\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBe able to do something like:\n\n```lua\nvim.wo.indentexpr = \"v:lua.vim.treesitter.indentexpr()\"\n```\n\nin order to use a tree-sitter derived indentexpr.\n\nI imagine this would work similar to the indentexpr from [nvim-treesitter](https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter/blob/main/lua/nvim-treesitter/indent.lua) and maybe could be based on the work done there.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
